# Docker Compose Lab — Full Production Stack

## What We Built

A fully working production-pattern web application using Docker Compose with:

- **Flask** (Python web app) — runs as non-root user, built with multi-stage Dockerfile
- **Nginx** (reverse proxy) — custom image, forwards traffic to Flask
- **Custom Bridge Network** — containers talk to each other by name using Docker DNS
- **Multi-stage builds** — slim, secure production images
- **Non-root user** — Flask never runs as root inside the container

**Traffic Flow:**
```
You (browser) → localhost:80
                    ↓
              Nginx Container (port 80)
                    ↓
              Flask Container (port 5000, internal only)
                    ↓
              Response back to browser
```

---

## Project Structure

```
compose-lab/
├── docker-compose.yml          → orchestrates everything
├── web/
│   ├── Dockerfile              → multi-stage build + non-root user
│   ├── app.py                  → Flask application
│   └── requirements.txt        → Python dependencies
└── nginx/
    ├── Dockerfile              → custom nginx image
    └── nginx.conf              → reverse proxy configuration
```

