## Docker Networking in This Lab

### What Happened Automatically

When you ran `docker compose up`, Compose:

```
1. Created network: compose-lab_app-network
   Type: bridge
   Subnet: 172.20.0.0/16
   Gateway: 172.20.0.1

2. Assigned IPs:
   Flask (web)    → 172.20.0.2
   Nginx          → 172.20.0.3

3. Registered DNS:
   "web"   → resolves to 172.20.0.2
   "nginx" → resolves to 172.20.0.3
```

### Why nginx.conf uses `http://web:5000`

```
Nginx config:  proxy_pass http://web:5000

"web"  → Docker DNS resolves this to Flask's IP (172.20.0.2)
          automatically, no /etc/hosts editing needed
          no hardcoded IPs
          if Flask's IP changes, DNS updates automatically

5000   → Flask's port inside the container

This is Container DNS — the same thing you proved
in the networking lab:
  ping container2 → FAILED on default bridge
  ping container2 → WORKED on custom bridge
```

### Port Exposure — Security Pattern

```
Service  │ Internal Port │ External Port │ Accessible From
─────────┼───────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────
Flask    │ 5000          │ NONE          │ Only Nginx
Nginx    │ 80            │ 80            │ Everyone

Flask is completely hidden from the outside world
Only Nginx can reach Flask (same network)
Users can ONLY reach Flask through Nginx
This is the correct production security pattern
```

---

## Real World Lessons Learned

### Lesson 1 — container_name blocks scaling

```yaml
# This BLOCKS scaling
web:
  container_name: flask-app   ← forces one specific name
                                 --scale web=2 fails

# This ALLOWS scaling
web:
  # no container_name
  # Docker auto-names: compose-lab-web-1, compose-lab-web-2
```

### Lesson 2 — version is obsolete

```yaml
# Old way (still works but shows warning)
version: '3.8'
services: ...

# New way (no warning)
services: ...
# Just remove the version line entirely
```

### Lesson 3 — depends_on is startup order only

```yaml
depends_on:
  - web
```

```
This means: start web BEFORE nginx
It does NOT mean: wait until web is healthy
If Flask takes 10 seconds to start
Nginx might still try to connect too early

For production use health checks:
depends_on:
  web:
    condition: service_healthy
```

### Lesson 4 — Non-root user confirmed

```bash
docker compose exec web whoami
→ appuser

# NOT root. This is correct.
# Every production container should return a non-root user here
```

