## Commands Summary Table

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `docker compose up -d --build` | Build images and start all containers |
| `docker compose down` | Stop and remove containers and networks |
| `docker compose down -v` | Stop + remove containers, networks, volumes |
| `docker compose down --rmi all` | Nuclear — removes everything including images |
| `docker compose ps` | Show status of all services |
| `docker compose logs` | Show logs from all services |
| `docker compose logs -f` | Follow live logs from all services |
| `docker compose logs -f web` | Follow live logs from one service |
| `docker compose exec web bash` | Open shell inside running container |
| `docker compose exec web whoami` | Run single command inside container |
| `docker compose run web python migrate.py` | Run one-off command in new container |
| `docker compose restart` | Restart all services |
| `docker compose restart nginx` | Restart just one service |
| `docker compose build` | Rebuild all images |
| `docker compose build web` | Rebuild just one service |
| `docker compose pull` | Pull latest images from registry |
| `docker compose up -d --scale web=2` | Run 2 instances of web service |

