## What This Proves You Can Do

After completing this lab you can:

```
✓ Write a multi-stage Dockerfile from scratch
✓ Create and use non-root users in containers
✓ Configure Nginx as a reverse proxy
✓ Write a docker-compose.yml for multi-service apps
✓ Use custom bridge networks in Compose
✓ Understand container DNS (service names as hostnames)
✓ Scale services horizontally
✓ Debug containers with exec and logs
✓ Clean up completely with down --rmi all
✓ Explain every line of every file to a hiring manager
```

This is the foundation of every production Docker deployment.
Flask + Nginx is the same pattern used at companies worldwide.
The only difference in production is adding a database service,
SSL certificates, and deploying to EC2 instead of localhost.

